d\\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-description\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Explore the vibrant coastal pet culture of Norfolk, featuring seasonal beach access at Ocean View and pet-friendly commutes on the Elizabeth River Ferry.\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"city-rich-description\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-description-paragraph\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Norfolk, Virginia, offers a vibrant coastal lifestyle for pet owners, blending historic charm with modern, dog-friendly amenities. The city is anchored by the \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L12\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"https://elizabethrivertrail.org/\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-link\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Elizabeth River Trail (ERT)\\\"}],null,\\\", a 10.5-mile multi-use path that serves as a social hub for local pups and their humans. Along this trail, the Chelsea district stands out with its pet-welcoming atmosphere, where spots like Smartmouth Brewing often host \\\\\\\"Pints and Pups\\\\\\\" events. For those seeking off-leash play, the \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L12\\\",\\\"4\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"https://www.norfolk.gov/parks\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-link\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Bea McLoughlin Dog Park\\\"}],null,\\\" in the Ghent neighborhood is a local treasure, prized for its mature leafy canopy that provides critical shade during Virginia’s humid summers. This urban sanctuary is just one of many facilities maintained by Norfolk Parks \\u0026 Recreation, ensuring that whether you are a military family near Naval Station Norfolk or a professional in a downtown loft, there is a dedicated space for your dog to socialize safely.\\\"]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-description-paragraph\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Navigating local regulations and unique transit options is key to a seamless Norfolk experience. One of the city’s most distinctive features is the pet-friendly Elizabeth River Ferry, allowing leashed dogs to enjoy a scenic water commute between downtown and Olde Towne Portsmouth. Beach lovers should head to Ocean View, where dogs are granted freedom on 7.3 miles of shoreline during the off-season (Labor Day through Memorial Day). To maintain this high standard of pet culture, the city requires all dogs over 4 months old to be licensed and vaccinated against rabies. For those looking to open new pet facilities, our \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L12\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/owner-resources\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-link\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"owner resources\\\"}],null,\\\" provide data-backed insights on Norfolk’s growing demand for premium services. From \\\\\\\"Bark in the Park\\\\\\\" nights at Harbor Park with the \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L12\\\",\\\"4\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"https://www.milb.com/norfolk\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-link\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Norfolk Tides\\\"}],null,\\\" to quiet sunset walks along the Hague, Norfolk remains a premier destination for Virginia’s active canine community.\\\"]}]]}],\\\"$L31\\\",\\\"$L32\\\"]}],\\\"$L33\\\"]}]}],\\\"$L34\\\",\\\"$L35\\\",\\\"$L36\\\",\\\"$L37\\\",\\\"$L38\\\",\\\"$L39\\\",\\\"$L3a\\\",\\\"$L3b\\\",\\\"$L3c\\\",\\\"$L3d\\\",\\\"$L3e\\\",\\\"$L3f\\\"]}]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"2b:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"footer\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"footer-new\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"footer-container\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"footer-grid\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"footer-column\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\