":\"VA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":7,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/pawsnickety-pets\",\"name\":\"Pawsnickety Pets\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/pawsnickety-pets\",\"description\":\"Pet parents in the area rave about Pawsnickety Pets.  What makes this dog facility special is its excellent, friendly, caring. The staff's dedication to creating a positive experience for both dogs...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Norfolk\",\"addressRegion\":\"VA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":8,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/petsmart-dog-training\",\"name\":\"PetSmart Dog Training\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/petsmart-dog-training\",\"description\":\"PetSmart Dog Training has become a favorite among the area residents.  What makes this dog facility special is its attentive, knowledgeable, spacious. The staff's dedication to creating a positive...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Norfolk\",\"addressRegion\":\"VA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":9,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/9-tails-pet-grooming-salon\",\"name\":\"9 Tails Pet Grooming salon\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/9-tails-pet-grooming-salon\",\"description\":\"Pet parents in the area rave about 9 Tails Pet Grooming salon.  What makes this dog facility special is its spacious, clean, safe. spacious indoor play areas Located in a safe area, This facility...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Norfolk\",\"addressRegion\":\"VA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":10,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/bayview-pet-salon\",\"name\":\"Bayview Pet Salon\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/bayview-pet-salon\",\"description\":\"Pet parents in the area rave about Bayview Pet Salon.  What makes this dog facility special is its clean, friendly, caring. The staff's dedication to creating a positive experience for both dogs and...\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Norfolk\",\"addressRegion\":\"VA\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"}}}]}3:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$c\"}}]\nd:T652,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Are dogs allowed on beaches in Norfolk, VA?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes—leashed dogs are welcome on all 7.3 miles of Norfolk’s public beaches, including Ocean View and Willoughby Spit, during the off-season (Labor Day through Memorial Day). During the summer season, pets are restricted to before 10 AM and after 6 PM to ensure safety during peak swimming hours.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Can I take my dog on the Elizabeth River Ferry?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Absolutely. Hampton Roads Transit (HRT) allows leashed dogs on the Elizabeth River Ferry, which connects downtown Norfolk to Olde Towne Portsmouth. It’s a unique, pet-friendly way to commute across the water while enjoying skyline views.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the main dog licensing rules in Norfolk?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"All dogs over 4 months old must be licensed with the City of Norfolk and have proof of rabies vaccination. Licenses are $10 for spayed/neutered pets and $15 otherwise. Note that the city also has a specific ordinance limiting households to no more than four dogs.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Which parks in Norfolk offer the most shade?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Bea McLoughlin Dog Park in Ghent is a local favorite specifically for its heavy tree canopy, providing essential relief during Virginia’s humid summers. Most other regional parks like Maplewood or Winona are also well-maintained by Norfolk Parks & Recreation.\"}}]}4:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$d\"}}]\n5:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Dog Parks Directory\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Norfolk\\\"}]}\"}}]\n6:[\"$\",\"$Le\",null,{\"variant\":\"light\"}]\n7:[\"$\",\"$Lf\",null,{\"items\":[{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"title\":\"City Overview\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-insights\",\"title\":\"Quick Facts\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-comparison\",\"title\":\"Top Comparisons\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-collections\",\"title\":\"Park Collections\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"neighborhood-clusters\",\"title\":\"Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-types-guide\",\"title\":\"Park Type Guide\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"map-and-neighborhoods\",\"title\":\"Map & Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"planning-essentials\",\"title\":\"Planning Essentials\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"expert-tips\",\"title\":\"Expert Advice\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-directory\",\"title\":\"Full Directory\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"owner-cta\",\"title\":\"Owner & Franchise\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"faq-section\",\"title\":\"FAQs\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"related-resources\",\"title\":\"More Resources\",\"level\":1}]}]\n8:[\"$\",\"main\",null,{\"className\":\"city-page-layout\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-button\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-trigger\",\"targetSelector\":\".table-of-contents\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-list-ul\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Contents\"}]]}]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"className\":\"city-hero-section \",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"section-shell city-hero-shell\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-hero-copy\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-breadcrumbs\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"children\":\"Home\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Dog Parks Directory\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"children\":\"Norfolk\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-eyebrow\",\"children\":\"City spotlight\"}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"children\":\"Dog Parks in Norfolk, VA\"}],\"$undefined\",[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-description\",\"children\":\"Explore the vibrant coastal pet culture of Norfolk, featuring seasonal beach access at Ocean View and pet-friendly commutes on the Elizabeth River Ferry.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-rich-description\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"Norfolk, Virginia, offers a vibrant coastal lifestyle for pet owners, blending historic charm with modern, dog-friendly amenities. The city is anchored by the \",[\"$\",\"$L11\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://elizabethrivertrail.org/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Elizabeth River Trail (ERT)\"}],null,\", a 10.5-mile multi-use path that serves as a social hub for local pups and their humans. Along this trail, the Chelsea district stands out with its pet-welcoming atmosphere, where spots like Smartmouth Brewing often host \\\"Pints and Pups\\\" events. For those seeking off-leash play, the \",[\"$\",\"$L11\",\"4\",{\"href\":\"https://www.norfolk.gov/parks\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Bea McLoughlin Dog Park\"}],null,\" in the Ghent neighborhood is a local treasure, prized for its mature leafy canopy that provides critical shade during Virginia’s humid summers. This urban sanctuary is just one of many facilities maintained by Norfolk Parks & Recreation, ensuring that whether you are a military family near Naval Station Norfolk or a professional in a downtown loft, there is a dedicated space for your dog to socialize safely.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"Navigating local regulations and unique transit options is key to a seamless Norfolk experience. One of the city’s most distinctive features is the pet-friendly Elizabeth River Ferry, allowing leashed dogs to enjoy a scenic water commute between downtown and Olde Towne Portsmouth. Beach lovers should head to Ocean View, where dogs are granted freedom on 7.3 miles of shoreline during the off-season (Labor Day through Memorial Day). To maintain this high standard of pet culture, the city requires all dogs over 4 months old to be licensed and vaccinated against rabies. For those looking to open new pet facilities, our \",[\"$\",\"$L11\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/owner-resources\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"owner resources\"}],null,\" provide data-backed insights on Norfolk’s growing demand for premium services. From \\\"Bark in the Park\\\" nights at Harbor Park with the \",[\"$\",\"$L11\",\"4\",{\"href\":\"https://www.milb.com/norfolk\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\"